							<p class="mb-3 italic">Balancing Contrast for Healthier Screen Exposure</p>

							<p class="mb-6">Acknowledging the hazards and risks associated with prolonged exposure to such extreme contrast levels is crucial, as it can strain vision, induce headaches, and impact overall well-being. To combat these issues, implementing ergonomic practices, such as regular breaks and adjusting screen settings to optimal contrast levels, can significantly alleviate the strain. Additionally, educating individuals about the importance of moderation in screen brightness and encouraging the use of specialized software or backgrounds tailored to reduce excessive contrast can mitigate the adverse effects of over-exposure. Creating awareness and providing accessible tools for better screen customization are key steps in addressing presenteeism and health risks linked to overexposure to high-contrast settings.
							</p>
							
							<p class="mb-3 italic">Unlocking Productivity</p>
							<p class="mb-6">
